-- South African Coal Export Prices Fall to Lowest in Three Months
-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 2012-10-01T09:10:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-01/south-african-coal-export-prices-fall-to-lowest-in-three-months.html
Coal export prices at  South Africa ’s
 Richards Bay , the continent’s biggest terminal for shipping the
fuel, declined to the lowest level in more than three months.  Coal for  immediate delivery  decreased $1.55, or 1.8
percent, to $84.61 a metric ton in the week ended Sept. 28,
according to IHS McCloskey data on Bloomberg. That’s the lowest
weekly price since June 22.  The price is quoted on a free-on-board basis, which
excludes delivery costs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marek Strzelecki in Warsaw at 
 mstrzelecki1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Lars Paulsson in London at 
